<subSubSection box="[197,1367,1191,1218]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1037,1952]" box="[197,1367,1191,1218]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,324,1191,1217]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[456,553,1192,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis box="[456,553,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but female genitalia with strong sclerotizations in the corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1037,1952]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,356,1230,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Description.</emphasis>
Ƥ Wingspan 
<quantity box="[526,662,1230,1256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21 mm</quantity>
. Forewing upperside ground colour deep straw yellow; pattern violaceous-grey. One basal dot; two basal bands fragmented; median and postmedian band and submarginal series of dots, a discal dot between median and postmedian band. Hindwing upperside ground colour light straw yellow. Forewing underside with a light pink suffusion in the basal and median areas; a small proximal costal portion is pink. Bands less distinct than on upperside. Hindwing underside as in upperside. Fringes of all wings yellow. Head yellow with violaceous-grey dot on vertex; labial palpi yellow, short, slightly inclined downwards; antennae ciliated, yellow. Patagia yellow, tegulae yellow with two dots. Thorax yellow with two dots on mesoscutum. Legs yellow, with the last (distal) tarsomere and pretarsus deep violaceous-grey; fore- and midlegs with distal portion of tibiae violaceous-grey. Spurs 
<number box="[950,1000,1540,1566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="0.2">0, 2</number>
, 
<number box="[1014,1033,1540,1566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
. Abdomen yellow. A 
<number box="[1296,1310,1540,1566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
large, not strongly sclerotized; A 
<number box="[427,440,1578,1604]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
small, interrupted by lamella postvaginalis. Female dorsal pheromone glands a bit longer than posterior apophyses. Male unknown. Female ostium large, without sclerotizations; membranous lamella postvaginalis. Ductus bursae cylindrical with conical sclerotized anterior end. Bursa copulatrix formed by a sub-conical cervix, from which the ductus seminalis arises, and by the corpus from whose posterior ending, laterally, a cone-shaped appendix arises. Distinct sclerotization at the appendix level: a subtriangular one, two irregular ribbon-like ones covered by small and strong thorns. Rest of corpus (anterior) globular and membranous, covered internally by small thorns and a small round dimple-shaped signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1037,1952]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,1848,1874]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[351,599,1849,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubitabilis">
<emphasis box="[351,599,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Afrasura dubitabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially thought by the author to be the female of the Nigerian males of 
<taxonomicName box="[261,473,1888,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis box="[261,473,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Afrasura indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the evidence overall supports its status as a new species. The specific name reflects the doubt about the original association.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
